At least 14 terms of life imprisonment as well as a total of 583 years imprisonment in 33 cases were investigated in 2016 alone.The KwaZulu-Natal Task Team together with the Specific Crimes, Serious and Violent Crime arrested a total of 55 suspects for various high profile cases such as armed robbery, murder, house robbery, theft, carjacking, business robbery and fraud.Brigadier Jay Naicker said during the same period the accused were convicted and sentenced by the various courts in the province after they were found guilty of the offences they had committed. The 55 arrested and convicted were linked to 33 cases that the team were investigating and those that were convicted and sentenced to life imprisonment were charged for murder cases, said Naicker.The team investigated high profile cases across the province including the policing precincts of Durban Central, Umbilo, KwaNdengezi, Marianhill, Amanzimtoti, Ixopo, Eshowe, Umlazi, Nqutu and Wentworth.The KwaZulu-Natal Acting Provincial Commissioner, Major General Bheki Langa congratulated the team of detectives for their outstanding work. We are pleased that we have such a team in the province who we can always rely on when we have high profile, serious and violent crimes within the province, said Langa.He added: These sentences are a clear indication that we have a very reliable capacity to deal with violent criminals in this province .-Aviwe Maxheke